    <description><![CDATA[
# Noetica

Noetica is a self-hosted AI dialogue management backend built for sovereign, cloud-free AI inference. It powers TurtleTerm's co-pilot NL-to-shell and intent routing.

## Features

- **22-intent dialogue layer** — routes queries to model, retrieval, slots, tools, surface, or skill handlers
- **HTTP API** on `localhost:8080` — `/health`, `/api/chat`, `/api/intent`, `/api/complete`
- **No cloud dependency** — fully local, air-gap compatible
- **TurtleTerm integration** — set `SOURCEOS_NOETICA_URL=http://localhost:8080` to use as co-pilot backend
- **Windows Service** — runs via NSSM as a background Windows service
- **22 intents**: chat, explain, fix, search, summarize, translate, codegen, debug, refactor, test, document, deploy, review, plan, recall, memorize, learn, compare, analyze, classify, generate, complete

## Quick Start

```powershell
# Start Noetica service
Start-Service Noetica

# Check health
Invoke-RestMethod http://localhost:8080/health

# Use with TurtleTerm
$env:SOURCEOS_NOETICA_URL = "http://localhost:8080"
turtle-copilot use noetica
turtle-copilot start
```

## API

```powershell
# Chat
Invoke-RestMethod -Method POST -Uri http://localhost:8080/api/chat `
  -ContentType application/json `
  -Body '{"message": "how do I list running processes on Windows?"}'

# Intent classification
Invoke-RestMethod -Method POST -Uri http://localhost:8080/api/intent `
  -ContentType application/json `
  -Body '{"text": "fix my failing tests"}'
```
